raw_entry:
JOHN CORPREW & JOSHUA CORPREW, 176 acs. of Cypress Swamp Land
in Norfolk Co., adj. their own high Land;
16 Jun 1756, p.9. £1.

WILLIAM DOBYNS, 194 acs. Lunenburgh Co. on the E or lower side of
Timber tree br., adj. Anders & Walton;
16 Aug 1756, p.48. £1.

JOHN GRIFFIN, 200 acs. Lunenburgh
Co. on both sides of Teway Homony Cr;
16 Aug 1756, p.56. £1.

WILLIAM GILL, 246 acs. Lunenburgh
Co. on both sides of Tewahomony Cr;
16 Aug 1756, p.60. £1.S5.

HENRY THOMAS, 275 acs. Southampton Co. on the S side of Nottaway Riv.;
adj. Jeremiah Ellis, Richard Vick,
Benjamin Faircloth & Joseph Newsom;
16 Aug 1756, p.123. £1.S10.

JOHN SNOW, 200 acs. Louisa Co. near
the great Mountains, adj. Mills & Garlix;
16 Aug 1756, p.172. £1.

JAMES SKEEGS, 82 acs. Augusta Co.
on a br. of new Riv. called Meadow Cr.;
16 Aug 1756, p.197. 10 Shill.

SAMUEL RIDGWAY, 400 acs. Albemarle Co. on both sides of Glovers Cr. a
br. of Slate Riv., crossing a fork of sd Cr;
16 Aug 1756, p.216. £2.

CHARLES EDWARDS, 420 acs. Brunswick Co. on the South fork of the Reedy
Cr.; adj. John Edwards, Smith & Clack;
16 Aug 1756, p.261. £2.85.

THOMAS DICKSON, 395 acs. Bedford
Co. on both sides of a br. of Falling Riv.;
13 Jun 1757, p.369. £2.

ROBERT RENNICKS, 90 acs. Augusta
Co. on Purgatory Cr. a Br. of James Riv.;
10 Nov 1757, p.391. 10 Shill.

JOHN ARCHER, 30 acs. Augusta Co. on
the Waters of Middle Riv. of Shanando;
10 Nov 1757, p.392. 5 Shill.

EDWARD WESSON, 1,154 acs. Brunswick Co. on both sides of Quarrel Sw.;
adj. William Johnson, Honycut &
Upchurch; 10 Apr 1758, p.427. £5.S15.

NICHOLAS COBB, 158 acs. Southampton Co. on the S side of the Cypress Sw.,
adj. William Cooper & Richard Murphy;
19 Aug 1758, p.461. £1.

JOHN ALLEN JUNIOR, 12 acs. Amelia
Co.; adj. Jones, Cocke, & Charles Irby;
19 Aug 1758, p.473. 5 Shill.

WILLIAM TOMMERSON / TOMINSON, 23’ acs. Lunenburg Co. on the
Brs. of Twittys Cr. adj. Jones & Comer;
19 Aug 1758, p.481. 5 Shill.

HENRY HOLLAND, 90 acs. Upper Par.
Nansemond Co., adj. William Holland;
19 Aug 1758, p.482. 10 Shill.

JOSEPH CABELL, 200 acs. Albemarle
Co. on Bishops Cr., adj. Francis Baker;
20 Sep 1759, p.630. £1.

MICAJAH CLARKE, 400 acs. Albemarle Co. on the North fork of Maple
Cr., adj. Marvel Stone & Margaret Stone;
20 Sep 1759, p.635. £2.

ROBERT HARDWICK, 300 acs. Albemarle Co. on both sides the North fork of
Hardware Riv., adj. Robert Lewis & Gay;
3 Mar 1760, p.707. £1.S10.

LEONARD PHILLIPS, 300 acs. Albemarle Co. on the head of Ivy Cr. in the
Hollows of a Mountain, adj. John Farrar;
3 Mar 1760, p.745. £1.S10.

THOMAS IVEY, 320 acs. Brunswick
Co. near a road, adj. Peterson & Parham;
29 May 1760, p.767. £1.S15.

THOMAS LEARWOOD, 230 acs. Bedford Co. on the W side of Elk Cr; adj.
Walton, Calloway, Williams & Kay/Hay;
29 May 1760, p.799. £1.S5.

JAMES CHAPPEL, JUNIOR, 150 acs.
Sussex Co. on the S of Blackwater sw;
adj. Captain John Mason, Mr William
Allen’s new survey & his Old lines, Mr
James Chappell Senior & William Hall;
10 Sep 1760, p.891. 15 Shill.

JOHN ARTHUR, 54 acs. Bedford Co. on
both sides of Goose Cr., adj. Richardson;
10 Sep 1760, p.896. 5 Shill.

HENRY KEY, 71 acs. Albemarle Co. in
Lackys thoroughfare, adj. James Lacky;
10 Sep 1760, p.901. 10 Shill.

JOHN THREADGILL, 212 acs. Brunswick Co. on the N side of Maherren Riv.;
adj. Hall, Henry Seward, Collier &
Nicholson; 26 Sep 1760, p.923. £1.S5.

JOHN DAVIS, 85 acs. Augusta Co. on
both sides of Jacksons Riv. by a Gully;
14 Feb 1761, p.987. 10 Shill.

WILLIAM BROWN, 240 acs. Lunenburgh Co. on both sides of Eaglenest Cr;
adj. Bowing, Hagood, Vaughan, Roberts
& Henry; 14 Feb 1761, p.998. £1.85.

RICHARD ADAMS, 400 acs. Lunenburgh Co. on the brs. of Great Louse Cr;
adj. John Waller, Wood Jones & William
Coldwell; 11 Jul 1761, p.1021. £2.
